messages.content:
Add file-backed report support to `send_message` and `report_done` in `src/mcp-server.ts`.

## Background

For long orchestrator→human results (code review reports, research summaries, multi-step plans), the full content shouldn't flood the S-Deck message feed. Instead: write the full report to a file, send a bus message with an executive summary + file path.

## Changes required

### 1. `send_message` tool schema (around line 97–121 in mcp-server.ts)

Add optional `report_file?: boolean` parameter:

```json
"report_file": {
  "type": "boolean",
  "description": "If true and to_id is 'human', write the full content to .synapse/reports/<timestamp>-<slug>.md and send a truncated summary with the file path instead. Use when the message is longer than ~20 lines.",
  "default": false
}
```

### 2. `send_message` handler (around line 380–392)

Extract the logic into a helper or inline it:

```typescript
const { to_id, content, priority = 5, report_file = false } = args as { ... };

if (report_file && to_id === 'human') {
  const reportsDir = join(process.cwd(), '.synapse', 'reports');
  mkdirSync(reportsDir, { recursive: true });
  const slug = content.split('\n')[0].toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, '-').slice(0, 40);
  const filename = `${Date.now()}-${slug}.md`;
  writeFileSync(join(reportsDir, filename), content, 'utf8');
  const lines = content.split('\n');
  const summary = lines.slice(0, 10).join('\n');
  const shortMsg = `${summary}${lines.length > 10 ? '\n…' : ''}\n\n[Full report: .synapse/reports/${filename}]`;
  sendMessage(AGENT_ID, to_id, shortMsg, priority);
  return { content: [{ type: 'text', text: 'Message sent (report filed).' }] };
}
// else: existing path unchanged
sendMessage(AGENT_ID, to_id, content, priority);
```

### 3. `report_done` tool schema (around line 334–342)

Add optional `report_file?: boolean` parameter:

```json
"report_file": {
  "type": "boolean",
  "description": "If true, write the full DONE report to .synapse/reports/<timestamp>-<slug>.md and send a short summary with file path to the human instead of the full content.",
  "default": false
}
```

### 4. `report_done` handler (around line 568–584)

```typescript
const { orchestrator_id, content, milestone, report_file = false } = args as { ... };

// Send full content to orchestrator always (they need it for synthesis)
const orchMsgId = sendMessage(AGENT_ID, orchestrator_id, content, 5);

// Human message: file it or summarize inline
let humanMsg: string;
if (report_file) {
  const reportsDir = join(process.cwd(), '.synapse', 'reports');
  mkdirSync(reportsDir, { recursive: true });
  const slug = content.split('\n')[0].toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g, '-').slice(0, 40);
  const filename = `${Date.now()}-${slug}.md`;
  writeFileSync(join(reportsDir, filename), content, 'utf8');
  const lines = content.split('\n');
  const preview = lines.slice(0, 5).join('\n');
  humanMsg = milestone ?? `DONE — ${preview}${lines.length > 5 ? '\n…' : ''}\n\n[Full report: .synapse/reports/${filename}]`;
} else {
  humanMsg = milestone ?? (content.length > 200 ? `DONE — ${content.slice(0, 200).split('\n')[0]}` : `DONE — ${content.split('\n')[0]}`);
}
sendMessage(AGENT_ID, 'human', humanMsg, 5);
```

## Key constraint

The full content ALWAYS goes to the orchestrator — the file option only affects the human-facing message. The orchestrator needs full detail for synthesis.

## Key files
- `src/mcp-server.ts` — all changes here

After implementing, run `tsc` to verify clean compile, then call `report_done` with a summary.
